						               													<description>Each player draws a start-destination-card and travels from west to east and back by using their stock of transportation chips (train, ship, car, plane, sled). Additionally, each player draws 3 city cards, which determine which cities he has to visit on his journey.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players take turns to roll 1 die and move their transportation chips on the corresponding spaces of the game board (blue = train, light blue = ship, green = car, orange = plane, yellow = sled). Each turn the players draw a quartet card. When the card pile is empty the players get a new traffic chip for each quartet collected. Three times per game the players may exchange cards to complete their quartets. On the spaces marked with a star, the players have to change their vehicle (transportation chip).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player back to his starting space wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
